Q: A rectangular piece of 150 sq m has a length which is 1m more than the 4 times the breadth. What is the perimeter of the piece?
Options: (a) 60 m (b) 61 m (c) 62 m (d) 63 m (e) 64 m
A:
Perimeter = 2(l + b) = 2(1m + 4b) = 2(1 + 4b) = 2(5b) = 10b. So the perimeter of the piece is 10b. Since the area of the piece is 150 sq m, the breadth is b = 150/10 = 15 m. So the perimeter of the piece is 10b = 150 m. The answer is (e).

