Q: Jim filled his dog's bowl with dog food. Starting at 8:00 am, Jim's dog ate exactly once an hour, consuming exactly 1/3 of the dog food remaining in the bowl at each feeding session. Approximately, what percent of the original food was in the dog's bowl right before the dog began to eat at noon of the same day?
Options: (a) 20% (b) 25% (c) 30% (d) 35% (e) 40%
A:
The dog ate exactly once an hour, so the dog ate 1/3 of the food at 9 am. At noon, the dog had eaten 1/3 + 1/3 = 1/2 of the food. So, the original food in the bowl at noon is 1/2 * 1/3 = 1/6 of the original food. So, the answer is (c).

