Q: A club consists of members whose ages are in A.P. The common difference being 3 months. If the youngest member of the club is just 7 years old and the sum of the ages of all the members is 250, then number of members in the club are :
Options: (a) 18 (b) 20 (c) 25 (d) 26 (e) 27
A:
Let the age of the members be n, where n is the number of members. Since the youngest member is 7 years old, the age of the club is 7 + n. The sum of the ages of all the members is 250, so the sum of the ages of all the members is n + (n-1) = 250. Hence, the number of members in the club is (250)/(n-1) = 27. So the answer is (e).

